In the Media

   Poets & Quants calls WHU's improvement of 23 places in the FT 2019 MBA
   Ranking "a good showing"

   article
   WHY WHU?

   WHU is one of the best business schools in Europe which is certified by
   high-quality accreditations (AACSB, EQUIS and FIBAA) and rankings.
   Excellent degree programs provide educational opportunities for every
   career stage supported by WHU’s renowned and highly international
   faculty. WHU offers a strong network of partner universities, companies
   and alumni and is truly international in all core areas of its
   activity. Studying and working at WHU is strongly influenced by the
   “WHU Spirit” – a feeling of social responsibility and mutual respect.
   DEGREE PROGRAMS

   WHU provides excellent educational opportunities for every career
   stage: a Bachelor program, a Master in Entrepreneurship, a Master in
   Finance and a Master in Management program, a Full-Time MBA, a Part-
   Time MBA and an Executive MBA, customized company programs, open
   enrollment programs and the possibility to pursue a doctoral degree and
   the German „Habilitation“.

WHU – Otto Beisheim
School of Management

About WHU

The Top International Business School in the Economic Engine of Europe!

   Which MBA? Executive MBA 2018
   The Economist

   Global MBA Ranking 2019

   Financial Times

Top in Rankings and Accreditations

   WHU – Otto Beisheim School of Management is a privately funded business
   school based in Vallendar/Koblenz and in Düsseldorf. It is a leading
   business school in Germany and is continuously ranked among the top
   business schools in Europe.

   WHU’s academic degree programs and executive education programs provide
   excellent educational opportunities for every career stage.

   more

Why WHU?

     * The best business school in Germany
     * Accredited by AACSB, EQUIS, and FIBAA
     * Truly international in all core areas of activity
     * High-quality academic programs
     * Strong network of partner universities, companies, and alumni
     * "WHU spirit“ based on social responsibility and respect

